init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States was hit particularly hard, with the majority of its major cities being destroyed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States government, in order to prevent another World War, decided to isolate itself from the rest of the world for 50 years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: However, as the years went on, and the world rebuilt itself, the fear of another war was gone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The year was 2052, and the United States was ready to re-enter the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Many people were afraid that the other nations would not honor the 50 year agreement and attack the United States, while others were afraid that the United States would

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The American government decided to come out of isolation, and see what the world was like.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The American government decided to send a team of diplomats to the United Nations to see what was going on.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When they arrived, they found the same thing, no signs of life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The diplomats decided to investigate the skeleton, and found a note in the pocket of the skeleton.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The American government was devastated by the news, but they had no choice but to accept it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The American government decided to let the populace know of the grim outcome, and to let them know that they were alone on Earth.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States was the only nation to survive the plague, and was the only nation to survive the war.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The American people were determined to make the world a better place, and to never let another World War happen again.
